  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nDealers are currently in a PIN regime with spot (6568.81) sitting just below the GEX flip at 6575, meaning they're likely buying the dip here as they're long gamma and providing stabilization. The massive positive gamma wall at 6580 (59.2B) creates a strong ceiling where dealers will aggressively sell any rally, while the 6575 flip level acts as the immediate pivot point for hedging direction. \n\nWatch for mean reversion back toward 6575-6580 range given the stabilizing regime, with the recent GEX surge (283% over 5min) indicating heavy option flow that should dampen volatility and keep price action range-bound between the 6550 support and 6580 resistance.",
